Anna Bjurstam




                          Anna Bjurstam                          Strategic Advisor






Anna Bjurstam has always been dedicated to Wellness, and has worked in the Wellness industry for 25 years. Together with her hands on expertise in Wellness and a Master Degree in Business, Anna has the unique combination of technical skill set and financial acumen which has led her to become a very well-known wellness profile, frequently asked to be the key note and guest speakers at conferences and events world-wide. Anna started her career being part of the launching Executive Team of S.A.T.S in Sweden, now the largest fitness chain in Scandinavia. She later ventured on to build Raison d’Etre Spas – a pioneering Wellness brand that has created more than 8 worldwide spa brands, including Raison d’Etre’s own LivNordic brand, and further consulted over 120 spas in 65 different countries. Today Anna oversees Six Senses Spas & Wellness, with 30+ locations world-wide, as well as Rasion d’Etre. She is a founding board member of Global Wellness Summit and is part of several wellness initiatives such as Global Wellness Institutes “Future of Well Work Initiative” and “Wellness Communities”. At Pegasus she is focusing on Wellness initiatives within the built environment, work places and hospitality especially concentrating on communities, sleep, nutrition, integrated wellness and spas.




