Costas Christ




                          Costas Christ                          Strategic Advisor






Costas Christ is one of the world’s top sustainable tourism experts whose work has taken him to more than 130 countries across six continents. He is an award-winning editor and columnist with National Geographic Traveler and also serves as Senior Sustainability Advisor for Virtuoso Ltd, the largest luxury travel trade network in the world. From 2004 – 2014, Costas was the Chairman for the World Travel and Tourism Council – Tourism for Tomorrow Awards, which recognize sustainable best practice travel companies and destinations.  He is the current Chairman for the National Geographic World Legacy Awards and is Sustainability Ambassador for Six Senses Hotels Resorts and Spas. Costas has been recognized as one of 50 Global Visionaries working to save the planet. His articles and essays have appeared in many of the world’s leading publications, including the New York Times, International Herald Tribune, and Sunday Times of London. He frequently appears on television and radio to talk about the global sustainable tourism transformation which he helped to spearhead. He has appeared on Travel Channel, Good Morning America, CNN International, BBC World, National Geographic Channel, National Geographic Weekend and National Public Radio, among others.  Costas is one of the pioneers of ecotourism, helping to officially define the term for the first time and serving as a founding member and former Chairman of The International Ecotourism Society.  His column in National Geographic has won the NATJA Gold Prize and Bronze Prize for three consecutive years ( 2012-2014) for best environmental travel writing. He was nominated for the Heinz Award, among the most prestigious United States awards given to an individual for their outstanding work supporting conservation, cultural heritage and the arts.




Education
