Mickey Beyer-Clausen




                          Mickey Beyer-Clausen                          Strategic Advisor






Mickey Beyer-Clausen is an entrepreneur and the co-founder and current CEO of Mental Workout, bringing together leaders in psychology and technology to help individuals improve their performance and well-being. Previously, he co-founded and served as CEO at Trunk Archive, a full service image licensing agency representing well known photographers. He also co-founded and served as Sr VP of Business Development of two leading domain name services, Speednames and Ascio Technologies. Mr. Beyer-Clausen founded Happiness Foundation, providing pro-bono consulting services to non-profits – which was co-financed by the Danish Government. He is on the advisory board of HealthCorps, founded by Dr. Mehmet Oz, to lead a nationwide movement toward a new generation of healthy young people.




