Dr. Alan Greene




                          Dr. Alan Greene                          Strategic Advisor






Renowned pediatrician and author Alan Greene, MD, is a leading authority and spokesperson on child health and wellness and a leading voice in health innovation. Dr. Greene is a graduate of Princeton University. He received his MD degree at the University of California at San Francisco. Upon completion of his pediatric residency program at Children’s Hospital Medical Center of Northern California he served as Chief Resident. He entered primary care pediatrics in January 1993. Dr. Greene is the Chief Medical Officer of Scanadu, a cutting edge health and technology company dedicated to empowering consumers with medical tools that educate in real time. Dr. Greene is the Founding President of the Board of the Society of Participatory Medicine (SPM) and has served as both President and Board Chair of SPM and Hi-Ethics (Health Internet Ethics), the non-profit organization formed to address privacy, advertising, and content quality issues for Internet health consumers. He has also served as an advisor to URAC for their health web site accreditation program. He is a founding member of the e-Patient Scholars Working Group, and a founding board member of the Center for Information Therapy. Dr. Greene is a member of the Board of Directors for Healthy Child Healthy World and The Lunchbox. Dr. Greene has been recognized by the Consumer’s Research Council as “One of America’s Top Pediatricians” for the last eight years, by Advance for Health Information Executives as one of the “Top 15 Most Influential Forces in Healthcare IT”, by Healthy Child Healthy World with the 2011 Prevention Award, and was named “The Children’s Health Hero of the Internet” by Intel.




Education
Princeton University; B.S, Philosophy of Science
University of California, San Francisco; M.D.



