Jennifer Hickman




                          Jennifer Hickman                          Strategic Advisor






Jennifer Hickman has had a multifaceted career having spent her early time of five years as a history teacher and Counselor at Phillips Andover Academy. After a brief period as a technology entrepreneur in Singapore, she returned to the U.S. and entered the real estate business.  Ms. Hickman spent six years as a principal of Cleveland Hickman Development Company, which focused on the development of urban transitional markets and senior living industry.  She also sourced real estate opportunities for a boutique investment bank.
Prior to joining Pegasus, she was the CEO of an agricultural company that developed food security initiatives in the UAE.  At Pegasus she is focusing on sourcing companies for investment in the food and water space and identifying and researching “best in class” sustainable technologies for agricultural production and the residential and commercial building industry. She is a Member of Sustainia100 Advisory Board. She is also an Advisor to Community Investment Management LLC which is an impact investment asset manager that provides institutional funding to U.S. small and medium sized business through virtual nonbank direct lending platforms, and IOU Central. CIM clients seek to earn a competitive financial return and achieve quantifiable positive social, environmental, and economic outcomes.




Education
Smith College; B.A., History



